<H1>Paranoia is Good</H1>
<H2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Password file stealing</H2>
<H3>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Old hat - BSD pwdb avoids it,</H3>
<H3>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;hides passwd encryption from /etc/passwd</H3>
<H3>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(master.passwd & pwdb only readable by root)</H3>
<H2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Password guessing</H2>
<H3>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;hide user names (mail rewriting)</H3>
<H3>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;OpenBSD logs failed logins (by tty/pty)</H3>
<H2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Firewall & server machines are not desktops</H2>
<H3>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;very few services</H3>
<H3>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Not X11</H3>
<H2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buy switches, not hubs</H2>
